# GenNews Backend — Implementation Plan

Build the complete Python/FastAPI backend for the GenNews news credibility platform, covering news aggregation, AI-powered analysis, story clustering, credibility scoring, and REST API.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Scaffolding

#### [NEW] [requirements.txt](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/requirements.txt)
Python dependencies: `fastapi`, `uvicorn`, `sqlalchemy`, `aiosqlite`, `feedparser`, `requests`, `beautifulsoup4`, `scikit-learn`, `sentence-transformers`, `transformers`, `torch`, `apscheduler`, `python-dotenv`, `httpx`

#### [NEW] [.env.example](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/.env.example)
Template for environment variables: `NEWS_API_KEY`, `LLM_MODEL_NAME` (default `Qwen/Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct`), `DATABASE_URL`, `FETCH_INTERVAL_HOURS`, `RSS_FEEDS` list.

#### [NEW] [config.py](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/config.py)
Central settings loaded from `.env` using `pydantic-settings` — API keys, DB path, scheduler interval, model names, RSS feeds list.

---

### Database Layer

#### [NEW] [database.py](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/database.py)
SQLAlchemy async engine + session factory for SQLite. `init_db()` to create tables.

#### [NEW] [models.py](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/models.py)
SQLAlchemy ORM models:
- **Article**: id, title, url, author, publisher_name, published_at, original_text, cleaned_text, keywords (JSON), category (JSON with confidence), misinfo_risk_score, llm_analysis (JSON: claims, tone, bias, framing), embedding (BLOB), cluster_id (FK), is_original_source, processed_at, status
- **StoryCluster**: id, title, summary, credibility_score, risk_indicators (JSON), created_at, updated_at, original_source_id (FK)
- **Publisher**: id, name, reputation_score, article_count, last_updated
- **FetchLog**: id, started_at, completed_at, articles_fetched, errors_count, status

---

### News Fetcher (Req 1 & 2)

#### [NEW] [services/news_fetcher.py](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/services/news_fetcher.py)
- `fetch_rss_feeds(feeds: list[str])` — parse with `feedparser`, extract title/link/published/summary/source
- `fetch_newsapi(api_key, query)` — call NewsAPI `/everything` endpoint
- `run_collection_cycle()` — orchestrator that calls both fetchers, stores raw articles, logs to `FetchLog`
- Error handling: per-source try/except, log failures, continue

#### [NEW] [services/scheduler.py](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/services/scheduler.py)
APScheduler `BackgroundScheduler` that triggers `run_collection_cycle()` every N hours (configurable).

---

### Text Preprocessor (Req 3)

#### [NEW] [services/text_preprocessor.py](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/services/text_preprocessor.py)
- `clean_text(html)` — BeautifulSoup to strip HTML, normalize whitespace/encoding
- `extract_keywords(text)` — TF-IDF via scikit-learn `TfidfVectorizer` on text, return top-15 keywords
- `preprocess_article(article)` — orchestrator that cleans + extracts, updates article record

---

### AI Analysis Pipeline (Req 4, 5, 6)

#### [NEW] [services/category_classifier.py](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/services/category_classifier.py)
- Zero-shot classification using `transformers` pipeline with `facebook/bart-large-mnli`
- Categories: politics, technology, health, business, sports, entertainment, science, world news
- Returns `{category: str, confidence: float, is_uncertain: bool}` (uncertain if < 0.6)

#### [NEW] [services/fake_news_detector.py](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/services/fake_news_detector.py)
- Heuristic + model approach:
  - Sensationalism score (exclamation marks, caps ratio, clickbait patterns)
  - Source citation check (presence of quotes, named sources)
  - Text-classification using a pretrained model or zero-shot
- Returns `{risk_score: float, indicators: list[str], is_high_risk: bool}`

#### [NEW] [services/llm_analyzer.py](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/services/llm_analyzer.py)
- Uses `transformers` pipeline with Qwen model (`Qwen/Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct`)
- Prompt engineering to extract: key claims, narrative framing, emotional tone, bias indicators
- 30-second timeout, fallback on failure
- Returns structured JSON `{claims: list, framing: str, tone: str, bias_indicators: list}`

---

### Similarity & Clustering (Req 7 & 8)

#### [NEW] [services/similarity_engine.py](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/services/similarity_engine.py)
- `sentence-transformers` (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`) to generate embeddings
- Cosine similarity for pairwise comparison (headline + body weighted)
- Store embeddings in article records

#### [NEW] [services/news_clusterer.py](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/services/news_clusterer.py)
- Threshold-based agglomerative clustering (similarity > 0.75)
- Assign article to highest-average-similarity cluster when multiple match
- Identify earliest article as original source
- Update existing clusters with new articles

---

### Credibility Scoring (Req 9, 10, 11)

#### [NEW] [services/credibility_engine.py](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/services/credibility_engine.py)
- **Publisher Reputation**: initialize at 0.5, weighted average of last 100 articles' misinfo scores
- **Credibility Score**: weighted formula combining:
  - Publisher reputation avg (30%)
  - Inverse misinfo risk avg (30%)
  - Source diversity factor (25%)
  - Consistency of claims (15%)
  - Single-source penalty: multiply by 0.7
- **Risk Indicators**: generate flags for single-source, low reputation, high misinfo, narrative inconsistency

---

### Processing Pipeline

#### [NEW] [services/pipeline.py](file:///c:/Farzi/Hackathon_Jims/backend/services/pipeline.py)
Orchestrates the full processing flow for a batch of articles:
1. Text Preprocessing
2. Category Classification
3. Fake News Detection
4. LLM Analysis
5. Embedding Generation
6. Clustering
7. Credibility Scoring

Each step has error handling — failures are logged, processing continues.

---

