## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **AI Models**: The plan uses HuggingFace models that will be downloaded on first run. The Qwen model (`Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct`) is ~1GB. The sentence-transformers model (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`) is ~80MB. The zero-shot model (`bart-large-mnli`) is ~1.6GB. These require significant disk space and initial download time.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **NewsAPI Key**: You'll need a free API key from [newsapi.org](https://newsapi.org/) to fetch articles beyond RSS feeds. The system will work with RSS feeds alone, but NewsAPI adds coverage.

> [!WARNING]
> **GPU vs CPU**: The models will run on CPU by default. Processing will be slower without a GPU. For a hackathon demo, consider using smaller batch sizes.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
1. **Server Startup Test**: Run `cd c:\Farzi\Hackathon_Jims\backend && python -m uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000` and verify the server starts without errors
2. **Health Endpoint**: `curl http://localhost:8000/api/health` — should return `200 OK` with component statuses
3. **API Endpoints**: Use browser subagent to test:
   - `GET /api/articles` returns valid JSON
   - `GET /api/clusters` returns valid JSON
   - `GET /api/publishers` returns valid JSON
   - `GET /docs` shows Swagger UI

### Manual Verification
1. Trigger a manual fetch cycle via `POST /api/fetch` endpoint and verify articles appear in database
2. Check logs for any processing errors
